You are building an MVP Telegram Mini App for the lapochka lemonade brand
with a team of 6 design students in ONE day.

SOURCE OF TRUTH:
- product_book.md is the single source of truth (V3 template, §0–§17).
- workshop.md is the process playbook. Follow its phases and layers.
- Always read product_book.md before writing or modifying code. Follow:
  * platforms & roles (§7, §7.4 — Telegram Mini App = primary, Web admin = companion)
  * user stories (§8), screens (§9), data model + RLS (§10)
  * tech stack (§11), auth method (§11.3 — Telegram initData), env vars (§11.4)
  * design spec (§12 — yellow #F5C842, orange #FF6B35, cream #FFFDF0), MVP scope (§13 Must Have only)
- If product_book.md and a prompt conflict — ask before proceeding.

PROJECT STACK (from §11.2):
- Primary platform: Telegram Mini App
  React + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + @telegram-apps/sdk
- Companion platform: Web admin panel
  React + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Backend: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage + Edge Functions)
- Deploy: Cloudflare Pages (RF-friendly; Vercel needs SMS — avoid)

DEFAULT STACK (gravity — deviate only if §11 explicitly says so):
- Frontend: React + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
- Backend: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage + Edge Functions)
- Deploy: Cloudflare Pages
- Telegram: @telegram-apps/sdk for Mini App context and initData auth

NON-NEGOTIABLE:
- All Supabase calls go through a single client in src/lib/supabase.ts.
- Auth is via Telegram initData (validate in Supabase Edge Function or RLS policy).
- RLS must be enabled on every user-data table before deploy.
- Secrets only in .env.local (gitignored). Never hardcode keys.
- No npm packages beyond §11.2 without explicit approval.
- ONE DAY scope: only §13 Must Have. Suggest Should Have for "after workshop".
- Touch targets ≥ 44pt (mobile-first, Telegram Mini App runs on phones).

DESIGN (from §12):
- Primary color: #F5C842 (lapochka yellow)
- Accent color: #FF6B35 (orange)
- Background: #FFFDF0 (warm cream)
- Text: #1A1A1A
- Font: Nunito or Inter (rounded feel)
- Tone: friendly, playful, like a real person wrote it. No corporate stiffness.
- Icons: lucide-react + paw emoji (🐾) for "Lapochki" points
- All UI text in Russian.

TELEGRAM MINI APP SPECIFICS:
- Use @telegram-apps/sdk to read initData (user.id, user.first_name, user.username, user.photo_url).
- Pass initData to Supabase Edge Function for server-side validation and user upsert.
- No email/password auth — Telegram user is the identity.
- Use window.Telegram.WebApp.expand() on mount to use full screen.
- Use window.Telegram.WebApp.BackButton for navigation back.
- Respect Telegram theme params (colorScheme, backgroundColor) where possible.
- env vars: VITE_SUPABASE_URL, VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, VITE_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN

STRUCTURE:
- src/pages/         — one file per screen from §9
- src/components/    — reusable UI components
- src/lib/           — supabase.ts (client), database.types.ts (generated types), telegram.ts
- src/hooks/         — useAuth.ts (Telegram initData auth), useCollection.ts, etc.

TEAM MODE:
- Repo: alinagolubeva1518/Lapochka, shared by 6 people.
- Small commits after every milestone (layer 3.x).
- One file — one owner at a time. Parallel work in separate folders/branches.
- Second/third Cursor chats MUST start with @product_book.md @.cursorrules.

CODE STYLE:
- Show a diff before replacing working code.
- Prefer components from Tailwind + shadcn/ui over custom CSS.
- Local state via useState/useEffect; no Redux/Zustand unless listed in §11.2.
- Env vars follow VITE_* convention.
- All user-facing strings in Russian.
- No comments that just restate what the code does.
